goals.question: What is the distribution of flight delays?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the frequency of flight delays and the range of delay times.

goals.question: What is the average distance of flights?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the distribution of flight distances and identify any outliers.

goals.question: What is the most common origin airport?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the airport with the highest number of flights departing from it.

goals.question: What is the most common destination airport?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the airport with the highest number of flights arriving at it.

goals.question: What is the relationship between flight delay and distance?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of delay vs distance
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is any correlation between flight delay and distance, and if longer flights tend to have more delays.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue', bins=30)
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flight delays?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Delay (minutes)")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(data=data, y='distance')
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    plt.axhline(avg_distance, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    origin_counts = data['origin'].value_counts().reset_index()
    origin_counts.columns = ['origin', 'count']
    chart = sns.barplot(x='origin', y='count', data=origin_counts, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the most common origin airport?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Origin Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['destination_count'] = data.groupby('destination')['destination'].transform('count')
    sorted_data = data.sort_values('destination_count', ascending=False).drop_duplicates('destination')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='destination', y='destination_count', data=sorted_data, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the most common destination airport?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Destination Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
